Kingdom Holding Rallies to Six-Week High on Zain Saudi Talks

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-05-24T08:55:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/kingdom-holding-rallies-to-six-week-high-on-zain-saudi-talks.html
Kingdom Holding Co. (KINGDOM)  rose to the
highest price in six weeks after the company controlled by Saudi
billionaire Prince Alwaleed bin Talal said talks to buy a 25
percent stake in Zain Saudi are still under way.  The shares climbed 5.1 percent to 9.2 riyals, the highest
intraday level since April 11, at 11:17 a.m. in  Riyadh .  Kingdom Holding and Bahrain Telecommunication Co.’s
negotiations to purchase the stake in Zain Saudi are “still
under way and all parties are committed to starting the due
diligence process and to concluding this transaction
successfully,” Kingdom Holding said.  Kingdom Holding and Bahrain Telecommunications made a joint
offer of $950 million to purchase Kuwait Zain’s 25 percent stake
in Zain Saudi Arabia. Zain Saudi shares rose 1.4 percent to 7.35
riyals.  Separately, Kingdom was allocated shares valued at $60
million in the initial public offering of Glencore International
Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
